OL,7,FBut his bosses said he couldn't accept
OL,8,Fthe gift because of the terms of his
OL,9,Fcontract. Luckily a holiday company
OL,10,Fstepped in and created a competition
OL,11,Fonly Paul could win.
OL,13,F"I'm over the moon!" Paul told ITV
OL,14,FNews London.
OL,16,F"I'm very grateful. So I'm very
OL,17,Fgrateful.
OL,19,F"I'm just doing my job - my everyday
OL,20,Fjob but they (residents) seem to
OL,21,Fappreciate it a lot."
